ure out what we want to be</span><hr size=1> Hi. I've been lurking on this board for quite a while now. It seems to be we have a problem with all of us getting together on the same page about what we want to be as a skald class. My hope is that we become more geared to a viking type class. That is our base class after all. I believe we should have more viking like abilities. This is what i posted on the vn board official skald thread.<br>
<br>
<br>
&quot;I think we are going about this all wrong. We need to think about realm balance before class balance. Everyone says 2.0 and shield spec is too powerful on a skald. I disagree. How many classes in alb can spec shield? answer is 5. How many classes in hib can spec shield. Answer is 3. How many classes in mid can spec shield? Answer is 2. Why is it that a realm that is geared more towards melee has the fewest classes that can spec shield? Alb has a stealth class that can spec shield. Both hib and alb have light tanks that can spec shield. I know what people will say. Light tanks dont put any points into shield. That doesnt matter. They still have the ability to spec it. Hybrids that don't have the ability to spec shield get some other form of defense. Wardens get bladeturn. Friars, zerks, savages, minstrels,valewalkers and bards get higher versions of evade and the dodger realm ability.<br>
<br>
I don't think speccable shield would infringe on thane abilities. Thanes have str as a primary stat  and get a self str/con buff. Thanes have repeatable casting spells that are single and aoe targeted. They have shout dmg spells also. Thanes have a higher lvl dmg add that stacks with our dmg add. They can choose to be in the frontlines or stay in the back and protect healers while they do casting dmg instead of melee. I am not pointing these things out to say that thanes are fine and dont need any help. I think they do need some more buffing up. I am just pointing them out to show the differences between our classes and that shield spec would not blur the lines between skald and thane.<br>
<br>
If we get 2.0 spec and spec shield it would round out this class nicely. The only other thing I would ask for is maybe power song and increased range on our dmg add.<br>
<br>
If we dont get shield then I would say some other form of defense would be needed. Possibly advanced evade and dodger. If this is all we get then I would say we need alot more tweeking also. Things like power song, dmg add range increase, reducing time on our dd spells to 15 secs and increase there range, and the suggested haste and self end regen/reducing usage abilities. Mid needs to have fighters that can survive long enough to do dmg.<br>
<br>
Our RA sucks. It needs to be fixed. Either the dmg needs to be seriously upgraded to counter albion and hib RA's or it needs to be put on infinite range and stack fully with all dmg adds.&quot;<br>
<br>
I know that this is not the most popular direction people want to go. Many people on that thread said shield would overpower skalds and I responded to them in that same thread. heres the link: <br>
<br>
 <!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://vnboards.ign.com/message.asp?topic=49950216&page=4">vnboards.ign.com/message....216&page=4</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--><br>
<br>
If a good majority of us can get together on some improvements for skalds other than just bug fixes I'll support it. Even if it is completely different from what I want. I think we have to get some sort of vision going here soon or we will get passed over if mythic decides to take a look at midgard soon.<br>
